	<!-- Duramax Content -->
	<div id="duramax-content" class="kit-content-section">
		<!-- Duramax Problem Section -->
		<section class="section section-light" id="problems">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="section-title" data-aos="fade-up">
					<h2>Common LLY/LBZ Duramax Problems</h2>
					<p>These are the critical issues our Duramax Solution Kit addresses</p>
				</div>

				<div class="problems-grid">
					<div class="problem-item" data-aos="fade-up">
						<div class="problem-icon duramax-icon">!</div>
						<div class="problem-content">
							<h4>EGR Cooler Failure</h4>
							<p>The EGR cooler can fail from coolant scaling, thermal stress, or heavy soot buildup, leading to cracks or restricted flow. Symptoms include unexplained coolant loss, white smoke, overheating, and related fault codes. Prevention involves regular coolant changes, keeping the EGR system clean, and using upgraded coolers when replacing.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="problem-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="50">
						<div class="problem-icon duramax-icon">!</div>
						<div class="problem-content">
							<h4>Head Gasket Issues</h4>
							<p>The Duramax LLY’s head gaskets can fail due to high cylinder pressures, often made worse by overheating or aggressive tuning. The factory head bolts can stretch under heavy load, allowing the heads to lift slightly and the gasket to blow. Symptoms include coolant loss, white smoke, overheating, and bubbling in the coolant reservoir. Prevention and repair typically involve replacing the gaskets with quality units, upgrading to ARP head studs, and ensuring the cooling system and EGR cooler are in good condition to avoid excess heat and pressure.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="problem-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
						<div class="problem-icon duramax-icon">!</div>
						<div class="problem-content">
							<h4>Top-End Sealing & Leak Prevention</h4>
							<p>Upper-engine gaskets and seals can wear out over time, causing oil leaks, coolant seepage, exhaust leaks, and intake leaks that reduce performance and allow unmetered air into the system. Symptoms vary depending on the leak location but may include visible drips, fluid odor, loss of power, or increased exhaust noise. Prevention includes timely gasket replacement and regular inspection for early signs of leakage.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="problem-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="150">
						<div class="problem-icon duramax-icon">!</div>
						<div class="problem-content">
							<h4>Preventive Reliability Upgrade</h4>
							<p>Weak factory head bolts, aging gaskets, and deteriorating EGR components can combine into a failure chain—starting with EGR cooler damage, progressing to overheating, and ending in blown head gaskets. Symptoms may include rising coolant temps under load, recurring coolant loss, or repeated top-end failures. Prevention involves proactively upgrading these components together to avoid cascading damage.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

